<TITLE> 2000 nurses to be recruited this month </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 12 (bdnews24.com)Two thousand new nurses will be recruited this month, according to the state minister for local government. Jahangir Kabir Nanak made the announcement at a meeting commemorating the International Nurses' Day on Wednesday. A ministry statement quoted Nanak as saying that the government had given importance to the health sector in the implementation of 'Vision-2020' and have taken special programmes. Nanak also said at a meeting, organised at the auditorium of Bangladesh Medical College Hospital's Dhanmondi campus, that another 3000 nurses will be appointed in the second stage. He urged non-governmental health institutions to increase the facilities of nursing profession alongside government efforts. Later, the junior minister cut a cake on the occasion of the birth anniversary of Florence Nightingale, the founder of professional nursing. The hospital's director professor Md Akther Morshed presided over the meeting attended by national professor Dr Nurul Islam and others. bdnew
